    {
      "id": "349319fe_793aa623",
      "file_path": "certService/helm/aaf-cert-service/templates/service-external.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 12,
      "message": "By wrong usage I mean - Values.containerPort by name suggests its port on container side, while \"port\" from K8s spec says - its a port on K8s service layer. It of course works, cause docker exposes 8080 port and \"targetPort\" is missing. Basically you are flatten K8s abstraction and always uses 8080 on K8s service layer, but if, e.g. you will reconfigure it to value 80, it won't work cause docker exposes 8080 port.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-12 13:47:06.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f964de56_1da01678",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "0d965a25_e5476ace",
      "file_path": "certService/helm/aaf-cert-service/templates/service-external.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 12,
      "message": "From my perspective, it's fine that \"Values.containerPort\" suggests container port, because that's my intention with that variable. It's intended to specify the container port in Deployment.\nHowever, because I don't want to specify a different port on Service, I use it also inhere.\n\nFor me, current implementation means \"For service port use the same port as in container\".\nSo I don't find it confusing, as far as someone is familiar with Kubernetes Service specification. \n\nDo you want me to split it into two sperate variables and explicitly declare port and targetPort here anyway?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3771,
        "name": "Adam Wudzinski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "adam.wudzinski@nokia.com",
        "username": "adamwudzinski"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-12 14:04:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "349319fe_793aa623",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "769ef9d7_9217017e",
      "file_path": "certService/helm/aaf-cert-service/templates/service-external.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 12,
      "message": "No, you can keep it as it is. I don't anticipate that we will change SVC port so often. Maybe never. Wanted to inform you where I see 'future' issue and that variable name vs usage place is misleading.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-12 14:37:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0d965a25_e5476ace",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "ad9a5f69_8730d4ba",
      "file_path": "certService/helm/aaf-cert-service/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 3,
      "message": "By convention you should provide two variables - repository and image. So split this into:\nrepository: onap-dev-local.esisoj70.emea.nsn-net.net\nimage: kasperki/cert-service:1.0.0\n\nand use: \nimage: \"{{ .Values.repository }}/{{ .Values.image }}\"\n\n\nAfter this change +1 from me.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-12 14:37:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
